{"title_page": "Simhachalam railway station", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name          = Simhachalam\n| native_name   = \u0c38\u0c3f\u0c02\u0c39\u0c3e\u0c1a\u0c32\u0c02\n| type          = [[Indian Railways|Indian Railway]] Station\n| style         = Indian railway\n| image         = Entrance view of Simhachalam train station.jpg\n| image_caption = \n| address       = Gopalapatnam,  Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, 530027\n| country       = India\n| coordinates   = {{coord|17.7452|83.2208|type:railwaystation_region:IN|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation     = 27 meters\n| line          = [[Visakhapatnam-Vijayawada section]] of [[Howrah-Chennai main line]]\n| other         = \n| structure     = Standard (on ground station)\n| platform      = 2\n| tracks        = [[Indian gauge|Broad gauge]] {{track gauge|1676mm}}\n| parking       = Available\n| opened        = \n| closed        = \n| rebuilt       = \n| electrified   = Yes\n| ADA           = \n| code          = {{Indian railway code\n  | code     = SCM\n  | zone     = [[South Coast Railway zone|South Coast Railway]]\n  | division = [[Waltair railway division]]\n  }}\n| owned         = \n| operator      = \n| status        = Functioning\n| former        = \n| passengers    = \n| pass_year     = \n| pass_percent  = \n| pass_system   = \n| map_type      = India Andhra Pradesh#India\n| map_caption   = Location in Andhra Pradesh##Location in India\n}}\n{{Visakhapatnam Railway|collapse=y}}\n'''Simhachalam railway station''' (station code:SCM), located in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]], serves Simhachalam in [[Visakhapatnam district]]. It lies on the [[Howrah-Chennai main line]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Durg-VSKP Passenger at Simhachalam 04.jpg|thumb|right|Durg-VSKP Passenger]]\nSimhachalam railway station is third busiest railway station in executive capital of Andhra Pradesh (Visakhapatnam) after [[Visakhapatnam railway station]] and [[Duvvada railway station]]. It mainly serves purpose to reach [[Simhachalam]] and the surrounding locale.\n\nBetween 1893 and 1896, {{convert|1288|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} of the [[South Eastern Railway Zone (India)|South Eastern Railway]] was opened for traffic. In 1898\u201399, [[Bengal Nagpur Railway]] was linked to the lines in southern India.<ref name=ser>{{cite web| url=http://www.ser.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,1| title=Major Events in the Formation of S.E. Railway| publisher=South Eastern Railway| accessdate=2012-11-10| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130401151628/http://www.ser.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0%2C1| archivedate=1 April 2013| df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nVisakhapatnam steel plant was established in the 1980s and the first coke oven battery was commissioned in 1989.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.vizagsteel.com/index.asp| title=Visakhapatnam Steel Plant| publisher=Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Limited| accessdate=2013-01-15}}</ref> South Coast Railway is the present operator.\n\n== Transportation ==\nSimhachalam railway station is well connected to all over Visakhapatnam.\n* '''BUSSES TO SIMHACHALAM''': (28H,28,28Z/H,6A/H,55H,540,549,6H)\n* '''BUSSES TO KOTTAVALASA''': (55K,28K)\n* '''BUSSES TO VIZAG RTC COMPLEX (BUS STATION)''': (6A/H,28H,12D,300C,28K,28A,28Z/H,333,555)\n\n==See also==\n*[[Waltair railway division]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://indiarailinfo.com/departures/simhachalam-scm/400 Departures from SCM/Simhachalam (2 PFs)] ''India Rail Info''\n\n{{s-rail-start|noclear=yes}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indian Railways}}\n{{s-line|system=Indian Railways|previous= Marripalem|next=Pendurthi|line= South Coast Railway zone|branch= Visakhapatnam-Vijayawada section  of [[Howrah-Chennai main line]]}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{Railway stations in Andhra Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in Visakhapatnam]]\n[[Category:Waltair railway division]]\n\n\n{{AndhraPradesh-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name          = Simhachalam\n| native_name   = \u0c38\u0c3f\u0c02\u0c39\u0c3e\u0c1a\u0c32\u0c02\n| type          = [[Indian Railways|Indian Railway]] Station\n| style         = Indian railway\n| image         = Entrance view of Simhachalam train station.jpg\n| image_caption = \n| address       = Gopalapatnam,  Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, 530027\n| country       = India\n| coordinates   = {{coord|17.7452|83.2208|type:railwaystation_region:IN|display=inline,title}}\n| elevation     = 27 meters\n| line          = [[Visakhapatnam-Vijayawada section]] of [[Howrah-Chennai main line]]\n| other         = \n| structure     = Standard (on ground station)\n| platform      = 2\n| tracks        = [[Indian gauge|Broad gauge]] {{track gauge|1676mm}}\n| parking       = Available\n| opened        = \n| closed        = \n| rebuilt       = \n| electrified   = Yes\n| ADA           = \n| code          = {{Indian railway code\n  | code     = SCM\n  | zone     = [[South Coast Railway zone|South Coast Railway]]\n  | division = [[Waltair railway division]]\n  }}\n| owned         = \n| operator      = \n| status        = Functioning\n| former        = \n| passengers    = \n| pass_year     = \n| pass_percent  = \n| pass_system   = \n| map_type      = India Andhra Pradesh#India\n| map_caption   = Location in Andhra Pradesh##Location in India\n}}\n{{Visakhapatnam Railway|collapse=y}}\n'''Simhachalam railway station''' (station code:SCM), located in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]], serves Simhachalam in [[Visakhapatnam district]]. It lies on the [[Howrah-Chennai main line]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Durg-VSKP Passenger at Simhachalam 04.jpg|thumb|right|Durg-VSKP Passenger]]\nSimhachalam railway station is third busiest railway station in executive capital of Andhra Pradesh (Visakhapatnam) after [[Visakhapatnam railway station]] and [[Duvvada railway station]]. It mainly serves purpose to reach [[Simhachalam]] and the surrounding locale.\n\nBetween 1893 and 1896, {{convert|1288|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} of the [[South Eastern Railway Zone (India)|South Eastern Railway]] was opened for traffic. In 1898\u201399, [[Bengal Nagpur Railway]] was linked to the lines in southern India.<ref name=ser>{{cite web| url=http://www.ser.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0,1| title=Major Events in the Formation of S.E. Railway| publisher=South Eastern Railway| accessdate=2012-11-10| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130401151628/http://www.ser.indianrailways.gov.in/view_section.jsp?lang=0&id=0%2C1| archivedate=1 April 2013| df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nVisakhapatnam steel plant was established in the 1980s and the first coke oven battery was commissioned in 1989<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.vizagsteel.com/index.asp| title=Visakhapatnam Steel Plant| publisher=Rashtriya Ispat Nigam Limited| accessdate=2013-01-15}}</ref>. South Coast Railway is the present operator.\n\n== Transportation ==\nSimhachalam railway station is well connected to all over Visakhapatnam.\n* '''BUSSES TO SIMHACHALAM''': (28H,28,28Z/H,6A/H,55H,540,549,6H)\n* '''BUSSES TO KOTTAVALASA''': (55K,28K)\n* '''BUSSES TO VIZAG RTC COMPLEX (BUS STATION)''': (6A/H,28H,12D,300C,28K,28A,28Z/H,333,555)\n\n==See also==\n*[[Waltair railway division]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://indiarailinfo.com/departures/simhachalam-scm/400 Departures from SCM/Simhachalam (2 PFs)] ''India Rail Info''\n\n{{s-rail-start|noclear=yes}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indian Railways}}\n{{s-line|system=Indian Railways|previous= Marripalem|next=Pendurthi|line= South Coast Railway zone|branch= Visakhapatnam-Vijayawada section  of [[Howrah-Chennai main line]]}}\n{{end}}\n\n{{Railway stations in Andhra Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in Visakhapatnam]]\n[[Category:Waltair railway divis